<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With the longest single engagement in the Orange County Performing Arts 
Center's eight-year history, "The Phantom of the Opera" grossed a record $7.3 
million, playing to 149,354 during the six weeks from July 22 through 
Saturday.A center official said Tuesday that paid attendance averaged 97.3% of 
capacity for the 54 performances (the potential gross was $7.45 million). In 
its final week, "Phantom" set a one-week record of $1.1 million with paid 
attendance of 99.9%. The previous record-holder was "Les Miserables," which 
grossed $954,779 during one week in September 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Compiled by Kathy Stickel 
</P>
