ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: PLACENTIA; PHOTO PRESERVATION CLASSES SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city will offer three photo preservation workshops to teach family 
historians how to maintain keepsake photographs. 
</P>
<P>
 Workshop leaders will demonstrate how to crop and mount photos as well as ways 
to creatively decorate albums. The workshops will be held from 7 to 9 p.m. 
Thursday and Sept. 29 and from 1 to 3 p.m. Sept. 25. All classes will be held 
in Room 7 of the Backs Community Building, 201 N. Bradford Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The fee for each workshop is $10, and participants are asked to bring six to 
10 photos for use in a cropping exercise. Advance reservations are required. 
For more information or reservations, call (714) 993-6084 or (714) 524-9012. 
HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
