ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; COUNCIL CANDIDATES FORUM AT EBELL CLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ebell Club of Fullerton is inviting the public to a City Council 
candidates forum Oct. 5 at the club. 
</P>
<P>
 All 25 candidates in both the Oct. 18 special election and the Nov. 8 general 
election are expected to participate. 
</P>
<P>
 Each candidate will be given two minutes to present two issues troubling 
Fullerton and offer plans to resolve them, Ebell Club officials said. In 
addition, candidates will have one minute each to respond to questions from the 
audience. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum begins at 7:30 p.m. The club is at 313 Laguna Road.MIMI KO 
