<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: PORTOLA HILLS; COUNTRY FAIR WILL FEATURE FARM SKILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A country fair co-sponsored by Trabuco Trailblazers 4-H Club will be held 
Saturday at the Santiago Equestrian Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair, from 2 to 6 p.m., will include demonstrations on sheep shearing, 
goat milking and horseshoeing, among other things. 
</P>
<P>
 Members of the 4-H Club who have qualified for the Los Angeles County Fair 
Horsemastership event will display their skills. 
</P>
<P>
 There will also be booths, food, a petting farm, pony rides and music by the 
country-Western group the Buckaroos. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair's feature event will be a "Barnyard Fashion Parade," during which 
animals will don costumes and be judged for awards. 
</P>
<P>
 The 4-H Club is a youth organization for children in kindergarten through 12th 
grade. 
</P>
<P>
 The Santiago Equestrian Center is at 18381 Santiago Canyon Road. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 857-4759 or (714) 854-0778. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
