<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; ANNUAL ARBORFEST SET AT UNIVERSITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Friends of the Fullerton Arboretum will hold the ninth annual Arborfest 
Oct. 15 in the arboretum at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 The day's events will run from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. There will be games, pumpkin 
patch tours, face painting and tours of an 1894 Victorian cottage that belonged 
to one of the city's first doctors, as well as plant and pumpkin sales. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, horse-drawn hay rides will offer tours of the 26-acre arboretum. 
The petting zoo there has goats, chickens, ducks, sheep, llamas and miniature 
farm animals. Pony rides will also be offered. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is free for children under 12 and for members of the Friends of 
Fullerton Arboretum. All other visitors will be asked for a $3 donation. Campus 
parking costs $3.MIMI KO 
</P>
