<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEMINAR ON WRITING REPORTS IS OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rancho Santiago Community College District will hold a seminar this month 
on writing effective reports. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminar, designed to show people how to write clear, concise reports that 
are well organized and free of jargon, will be held on Mondays and Wednesdays, 
Sept. 19 to 28, from 8 to 11:50 a.m. Classes will be held in Building A of the 
Orange County Social Service Agency, 1928 S. Grand Ave., spokesman Dale Ruhe 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost of the seminar is $5.20, and $20 for those with advanced degrees. 
Registration is on a first-come, first-served basis. For more information, call 
(714) 564-6756. Participants should ask for ticket number 90660 when 
registering, Ruhe said. 
</P>
