<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; ACROSS THE NATION; ERICKSON: WALSH HAS LEFT 
MIAMI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Redshirt sophomore quarterback Chris Walsh has withdrawn from Miami, Coach 
Dennis Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Where he is going to transfer, I don't know," Erickson said. "I didn't want 
him to leave, but I wanted him to do what he thinks is best." 
</P>
<P>
 Walsh, brother of former Miami All-American Steve Walsh, returned to his home 
in St. Paul, Minn., according to Erickson. 
</P>
<P>
 After redshirting his first year with the program, Walsh played one game in 
1993, serving as a backup to Frank Costa and Ryan Collins. 
</P>
