</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: HUGE STRIPER TAKES BAIT AT SILVERWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Of the thousands of fish to come out of Southland reservoirs this past week, 
one fish stands out: a 48-pound 13-ounce striped bass pulled from Silverwood 
Lake. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Harleman of Norco fooled the fish with an anchovy while fishing aboard 
his boat at about 5 p.m. last Friday. The striper, a lake record, measured 47 
1/4 inches and had a 32 1/2-inch girth. 
</P>
