<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Housing Completions Decline: The number of new homes finished and ready for 
occupancy fell for a second straight month in July, adding to signs that 
housing activity is leveling off, the Commerce Department said. Completions 
fell 4.4% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.27 million after a revised 
drop of 7.8% in June, previously reported as an 8.2% decline. The government's 
monthly measure of housing completions is not as closely watched as its report 
on construction starts, but it is useful as a monitor of overall activity in 
the home building industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
