<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: BOARD TO DISCUSS SCAT FUND SHORTFALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Anticipated funding shortages for bus service to Ventura and Oxnard are 
scheduled to be discussed at a meeting of the South Coast Area Transit board 
today. 
</P>
<P>
 Board members will consider a five-year funding plan for the bus service, 
which predicts a deficit for service to Ventura in 1996 and a shortfall for 
service to Oxnard in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
 The board will also hold a public hearing on its $9.2-million budget for the 
current fiscal year. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting wil be held at 10 a.m. at the SCAT office, 301 E. 3rd St., Oxnard. 
For information, call 487-4222. SARA CATANIA 
