KOCHEL QUESTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Teachers and school administrators are mandated reporters of child abuse, 
sexual molestation and neglect. The Welfare and Institutions Code requires them 
to report all suspected instances. 
</P>
<P>
 If Ventura School District officials are claiming they did not have evidence, 
then they violated the law by not reporting the case of Coach Harvey Kochel 
case when they admit they warned him. Why is the school district hiring 
teacher/coaches with predatory, macho attitudes toward students rather than 
being protective and responsible? 
</P>
<P>
 The Times in each article written on this issue has described what went on as 
"an affair," "fooling around," or a "sex scandal." When are the newspapers 
going to accept the responsibility for calling a teacher's predation of a child 
what it is, sexual abuse and exploitation? 
