<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: RESEDA; ADULT SCHOOL OFFERS NEW SERVICES, CLASSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Classes in lip-reading and desktop publishing, a prep course for the National 
Council Licensure Examination for nurses and a new citizenship center are among 
the new services offered through the Reseda Community Adult School. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're trying to serve the community in areas that really need additional 
services, like older adults," said Principal Martin Conroy. 
</P>
<P>
 The adult school has about 30 branches, with four to six classes devoted to 
developmentally disabled adults, and will be offering additional refresher 
courses, Conroy said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lip-reading will be taught in conjunction with American Sign Language and 
hearing-loss compensation techniques on Friday afternoons starting Sept. 16 at 
the Menorah House in Reseda. 
</P>
<P>
 The nursing review course starts Sept. 20 at the adult school campus. 
</P>
<P>
 Tuition for the Reseda Community Adult School is always free, but there are 
small registration fees for some of the courses. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (818) 343-1977. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
