<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON TURNBULL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Pierre-Masson has been named boys' soccer coach and Mark Zulauf girls' 
tennis coach at La Quinta, Athletic Director Jim Perry announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Masson takes over for Craig Cummings, rejoining La Quinta after a four-year 
layoff. Masson guided the Aztecs from 1982-90 and they were the Southern 
Section Division 2-A co-champion in 1983, tying Bishop Montgomery, 1-1, in the 
title game. 
</P>
<P>
 Zulauf replaces Arnold Truong, who stepped down for personnel reasons. Truong 
headed the team for three years, winning two league championships and making 
three playoff appearances. 
</P>
<P>
 Zulauf was La Quinta's badminton coach in 1991 and is a math teacher at the 
school. DON TURNBULL 
