DISTRICT PANELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Newport-Mesa Unified School District is seeking volunteers to serve on its 
budget advisory and audit committees. 
</P>
<P>
 Eight of 14 seats are available on the budget committee, the school board's 
conduit to the community on matters related to the district's annual financial 
plan.Members communicate community desires to the board for fiscal planning. 
</P>
<P>
 There is one vacancy on the 15-member audit committee, which works with 
district auditors in preparing the annual report for the board and evaluates 
auditors' methods and effectiveness. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants for the audit panel need not have children attending district 
schools but should have financial or business experience and must live within 
the Costa Mesa High School attendance area. 
</P>
<P>
 To apply for either panel, residents of the district are asked to send a 
letter to the office of Supt. Mac Bernd, 1601 16th St., Newport Beach, Calif. 
92663. The application deadline is Thursday. For more information, call the 
superintendent's office at (714) 760-3500. HOLLY J. WAGNER 
