<P>
 Officials for the Santa Ana Unified School District are reminding students and 
parents that its weapons hot line remains open for the 1994-95 school year, 
which begins Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The hot line number for reporting students carrying weapons is (800) 
NO-2-GUNS. 
</P>
<P>
 Stickers bearing the number are on public telephones at the district's middle 
and high schools, and signs are posted in school offices. Notices regarding the 
hot line have also been sent to parents, district spokeswoman Diane Thomas 
said. 
</P>
