<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SADDLEBACK HAS NEW JAZZ BAND DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback College has a new director for its jazz band. 
</P>
<P>
 Bob Avzaradel takes over the position vacated by Paul Kurokawa, who left 
Saddleback to become chairman of the jazz department at Grossmont College in 
San Diego County. 
</P>
<P>
 Avzaradel was director of instrumental music at San Clemente High School for 
eight years. In 1987, he was honored at the Fullerton College Jazz Festival as 
most outstanding new jazz educator. 
</P>
<P>
 Most recently, Avzaradel was director of bands at Irvine High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Avzaradel is a former member of the U.S.A. Youth All Star Jazz Ensemble, which 
performed in Europe. He is a member of the National Assn. of Jazz Educators and 
the Southern California School Band and Orchestra Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 The Saddleback College jazz band consists of college and high school students 
and other local residents. 
</P>
<P>
 For information about joining the band, call (714) 582-4747. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
