<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; HARTSHORN TO HEAD RED CROSS CHAPTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Terry Hartshorn of Corona del Mar, chairman of the board for PacifiCare Health 
Systems, has been elected chairman of the American Red Cross Orange County 
Chapter board of directors for 1994-95. 
</P>
<P>
 Also elected as executive officers were Robert L. Wenzel, an Irvine attorney, 
human resources vice chairman; Robert Olson of Yorba Linda, president of R.D. 
Olson Construction, revenue generation vice chairman; and Robert Conway of 
Irvine, a partner with KPMG Peat Marwick, treasurer. 
</P>
<P>
 Vice chairman of community relations is Leo Brennan of Laguna Niguel, vice 
president and general manager of Dimension Cable; the legal counsel is Robert 
A. Wilson, a Santa Ana attorney with Orchids Paper Products Co.; and the 
secretary is Robert McClain of Huntington Beach, who is with Betson Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
 The local chapter of the American Red Cross is headquartered in Santa Ana. 
Among the programs offered are disaster emergency services, HIV/AIDS education, 
health and safety training and services to military families. ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
