<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; PRIVATE-PARK USE BY CITY BEING EXAMINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At the suggestion of Mayor R. Craig Scott, the city's Parks and Recreation 
Department is considering the possibility of staging recreational events at 
some private parks to increase participation by residents. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott has asked the department to look into the feasibility of sponsoring 
summer concerts or day camps for youths in the private parks at Nellie Gail 
Ranch and Moulton Ranch housing developments. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott, who lives in Nellie Gail Ranch, says many of his neighbors don't turn 
out for city-sponsored events because the public parks are too far from their 
homes. 
</P>
<P>
 "People will be more likely to participate if events are in their 
neighborhood," Scott said. "I would like to see the fine services of parks and 
recreation available to all the citizens of Laguna Hills." 
</P>
<P>
 Parks and Recreation Director Dave Lewis said it will be several months before 
officials decide whether to begin sponsoring events at the private parks. LYNN 
FRANEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
