<P>
VAN STRIKES THREE SIBLINGS; ONE IS CRITICALLY INJURED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 3-year-old boy was in critical condition Tuesday night after a mini-van 
struck him and his two siblings as they crossed a street with their mother, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Leticia Leos, 34, was crossing 1st Street near Oak Street with her three 
children about 5:54 p.m. when a westbound vehicle hit the youngsters, said Sgt. 
Don Robertson of the Santa Ana Police Department.The mother, who was not 
injured, and her children were apparently not in a crosswalk, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 3-year-old boy suffered a broken collarbone and head injuries and was 
taken to Western Medical Center-Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 His 3-year-old sister and a 4-month-old brother, who was in a stroller, 
received minor injuries, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police questioned the driver and released him. He was not cited. 
</P>
