<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHANNEL PARADE OF BOATS TO LAUNCH SEAFEST; CELEBRATION: JOHN WAYNE FILMS AND 
THE BALBOA ARTS AND MUSIC FESTIVAL WILL BE PART OF THE YEARLY FESTIVITIES. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Newport Harbor Area Chamber of Commerce will host its annual Seafest 
starting this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Events scheduled for opening night, Friday, include a John Wayne film 
festival. The screening begins at 6 p.m. at the Edwards Fashion Island Cinemas, 
and there will be a second showing at noon Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Seafest will also feature a free parade for the eighth annual Wooden Boat 
Festival. The event starts at 5 p.m. at the entrance to Newport Harbor and will 
run up the main channel to the Lido Village turning basin. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday highlights include the Balboa Arts and Music Festival from 9 a.m. to 
6 p.m. at the foot of the Balboa Pier. Dozens of local artisans will show off 
their creations of jewelry, paintings, dolls, woodworks and pottery against a 
backdrop of music and dance performances. 
</P>
<P>
 The day's music schedule begins with a children's program called "Dance City" 
at 10 a.m. and a children's concert by singer Greggy Dee at 10:30 a.m. The 
music will take a Latin turn at 11:45 a.m., when the Susie Hansen Band 
performs. Oasis Senior Center's Ukelele Strummers will perform music from the 
1930s at 1 p.m., followed by a surf band, the Chantays, at 1:45 p.m. Big band 
music takes the stage at 4 p.m. with the Sounds of Swing. 
</P>
<P>
 Also on Saturday, adventurous pairs can take their chances constructing 
vessels and racing them on a short course around a buoy in the Nail & Sail Boat 
Building Contest. Landlubbers can tour tall ships and other wooden boats. 
Sailors can show off their skills and compete for prizes in the sailboat 
regatta from 11:30 a.m. to 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Children's events scheduled for both Saturday and Sunday include the Davey's 
Locker fishing tournament, a "Pog Party," a model boat building school and a 
costume contest from 2 to 4 p.m. On Sunday, the Balboa Branch Library will host 
a children's program at 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday-only events include a sandcastle contest at Corona del Mar State Beach 
from noon to 3 p.m., outrigger canoe racing at Newport Dunes from noon to 6 
p.m. and a "White Linen and Jazz" performance at the Hyatt Newporter 
Amphitheater from 4 to 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Other events include an antique symposium on Via Oporto and Central Avenue in 
Lido from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. Thursday through Sunday at Marina Village; the sixth 
annual Taste of Newport restaurant festival Friday through Sunday at Fashion 
Island; a kite festival from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Saturday and Sunday at Balboa 
Peninsula Park; the Pier Swim at 11 a.m. Saturday, followed by the Voyagers 
Celebrity Yacht Club Challenge at 1 p.m., both at Newport Pier; and the Newport 
Seafest 8K, 4K and 2K runs from 8 a.m. to noon Sunday at Newport Dunes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
