<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: CARELINE PLANS TO BUY 2 CHICAGO-AREA FIRMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CareLine Inc. said Tuesday it has signed letters of intent to buy two 
ambulance service providers in the Chicago area. 
</P>
<P>
 CareLine, based in Irvine, is now the nation's second-largest ambulance 
service company. Its addition of TEK Ambulance and Rescue Eight Paramedic 
Services will mark its entry into the Illinois market and will expand its 
operations to 10 states. 
</P>
<P>
 CareLine did not disclose the terms of the deal. It did say that the two 
Chicago-area companies had total 1993 revenue of more than $13 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA090794-0234 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 076863 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
September 7, 1994, Wednesday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 6; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
