<TEXT>
<P>
 Strategic Mortgage Services Inc.: The firm, which provides services to 
mortgage lenders, said Tuesday it has acquired an Ohio company that compiles 
lending and geographic information. 
</P>
<P>
 Strategic Mortgage, based in Costa Mesa, sells title insurance and provides 
appraisal services and credit reports. Geotrac Inc., the company it is 
acquiring, tells mortgage lenders whether a property sits in a flood zone, thus 
requiring the prospective owner to purchase flood insurance. It also tracks 
compliance with the Home Mortgage Disclosure Act. 
</P>
<P>
 Terms of the deal, which was completed Friday, were not disclosed. 
</P>
